		"notes": [
			{
				"category": "summary",
				"text": "Release of OpenShift Serverless Client kn 1.19.0\n\nRed Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Moderate. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.",
				"title": "Topic"
			},
			{
				"category": "general",
				"text": "Red Hat OpenShift Serverless Client kn 1.19.0 provides a CLI to interact with Red Hat OpenShift Serverless 1.19.0. The kn CLI is delivered as an RPM package for installation on RHEL platforms, and as binaries for non-Linux platforms.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* golang: net/http/httputil: panic due to racy read of persistConn after handler panic (CVE-2021-36221)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
				"title": "Details"
			},
			{
